** At Powerlink, every possibility starts with you **

We believe life's about possibilities. And so is the future. That's why we
need you.

We're working at the heart of Queensland's energy transformation. Now more
than ever, we need people who want to help us deliver a world-class energy
future and ensure we continue to navigate through this once in a generation
energy challenge. Join us and make it happen.

** Life at Powerlink **

As Business Architect, you'll help us connect a more sustainable energy future
for more than five million Queenslanders and 253,000 businesses. Your work
with us is about every light turned on, every community connected, and every
future made possible.

  * We offer robust leadership development through integrated programs, fostering growth across all levels. 
  * You will be rewarded with a competitive remuneration + 12.75% superannuation. 
  * Health & wellbeing benefits, including corporate health plan with employee discounts, annual flu vaccinations. 
** Find a career that matters and lasts **

As the Business Architect, you will provide business architecture services to
implement strategy, improve business efficiency and agility and be
instrumental in building a knowledge base which forms the fabric of innovation
and decision making within the organisation.

  
Specifically, you will:  

  * Develop and maintain business architecture artefacts and data including blueprints, models, roadmaps and other artefacts or oversee the production and implementation of architecture solutions and operating models. 
  * Co-design and assure business architecture artefacts and business process models produced by third parties. 
  * Develop and maintain business architectural artefacts, such as capability models, value chains and business object data and their relationships that can be used by the business and projects to understand and analyse the business. 
  * Provide input and assurance of enterprise architecture artefacts including strategies, position papers and direction statements. 
  * Work with the Senior Business Architect as well as solution and technical architecture representatives to define current, transition, and target state architectures in line with architecture principles, enterprise and IT strategies and enterprise priorities. 
** The community you will join **

Based in Brisbane, you will be joining the Strategic Architecture, Engagement
& Assurance team within the Business IT & Digital Delivery group. This team
thrives on a culture of high performance, where each member's dedication to
excellence is complemented by a strong emphasis on collaboration, ultimately
fostering a dynamic and achievement-oriented environment.  

** Your expertise **

  * Degree level qualification in a related discipline to this role, or a lesser qualification coupled with relevant experience. 
  * Evidence of completion of training within Business Architecture discipline delivered by a recognised organisation. 
  * Demonstrated experience in a business architecture or adjacent role developing architectural artefacts and maintaining business concept data involving enterprise models such as capability models, value chains and service model blueprints. 

We'd also love you to have:

  * Recent experience utilising business architectural disciplinary techniques to facilitate changes in some or all of the following: operating model, organisation structure, roles, service design, business process, data and business systems. 
  * Certification or eligibility to gain certification as a Certified Business Architect within the Business Architecture Guild. 
  * Enterprise Architecture Certification (e.g.TOGAF) or actively progressing towards this certification. 
